token_lists.title: Cellular Stains - Detonation
token_lists.description: In Cellular Stains, colors spread and blend in twisted, surnatural ways. Sometimes, strange landscapes or ominous structures emerge from the colorful mess. Does our tendency to interpret noise lead us to hallucinate these fantastic places? Or is the machine trying to show us glimpses of another world?

token_lists.title: HOKJES
token_lists.description:
In HOKJES we ask the question of why we as people always categorize things and never stop to think on why this is and if its still relevant to do so.
The works represent the feeling of flowing through life but always walking against the invisible frames (hokjes). We got inspired by abstract works and the idea of the liminal space between the physical and digital worlds. For us this is a great tool to make these mostly hidden parts of society aparant and tangible and to express our thoughts about them in an indirect manner.
In the end its all about being who you are, but to get there you first have to identify and actively push through the HOKJES.
